# Quality Reference: DESIGN.md Structure

This is the target quality bar for every DESIGN.md output.
Based on the Apple design system documentation from getdesign.md.

## Required Sections (9 minimum)

### 1. Visual Theme & Atmosphere
- Narrative description of the brand's design philosophy
- Key characteristics as bullet list
- NOT a token dump -- this is editorial writing about what makes the design distinctive

### 2. Color Palette & Roles
- Organized by role: Primary, Interactive, Text, Surface, Button States, Shadows
- Each color: name, hex, CSS variable if any, specific usage context
- NOT just a flat list of hex values

### 3. Typography Rules
- Font family with fallback stacks
- Full hierarchy TABLE: Role | Font | Size | Weight | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Notes
- Principles section explaining the typography philosophy

### 4. Component Stylings
- Buttons: every variant with exact CSS (bg, text, padding, radius, border, font, hover, active, focus)
- Cards & Containers: bg, border, radius, shadow, content alignment, hover
- Navigation: bg, height, text style, active state, logo, mobile behavior
- Image Treatment: how images are handled (solid bg, full-bleed, rounded corners)
- Distinctive Components: brand-specific patterns (hero module, product grid, comparison strip)

### 5. Layout Principles
- Spacing System: base unit, full scale
- Grid & Container: max width, column layout, gutter
- Whitespace Philosophy: how space is used intentionally
- Border Radius Scale: micro through full pill

### 6. Depth & Elevation
- Table: Level | Treatment | Use
- Shadow Philosophy: when and why shadows are used
- Decorative Depth: glass effects, color transitions, product shadows

### 7. Do's and Don'ts
- Concrete rules with reasoning
- "Do use X for Y" / "Don't use X because Z"
- At least 8 Do's and 8 Don'ts

### 8. Responsive Behavior
- Breakpoints TABLE: Name | Width | Key Changes
- Touch Targets: minimum sizes
- Collapsing Strategy: how components adapt
- Image Behavior: scaling, cropping rules

### 9. Agent Prompt Guide
- Quick Color Reference: list of key colors with roles
- Example Component Prompts: 4-5 concrete prompts showing exact values
- Iteration Guide: numbered rules for consistency checking
